        <TextView
            android:layout_width="match_parent"
            android:layout_height="wrap_content"
            android:padding="10dp"
            android:text="3.Does mineral water taste differently from other types of water?
"
            android:textColor="@color/colorPrimary"
            android:textSize="16sp"
            android:textStyle="bold" />

        <View
            android:layout_width="match_parent"
            android:layout_height="1dp"
            android:background="@color/colorPrimaryDark" />

        <TextView
            android:textColor="@color/colorPrimary"

            android:layout_width="match_parent"
            android:layout_height="wrap_content"
            android:lineSpacingExtra="8dp"
            android:padding="15dp"
            android:text="          Absolutely!  The quality and quantity of minerals in every genuine mineral water brand is different and unique, as it depends on the source of water.  These minerals impart a taste to water which is lacking in distilled water or other de-mineralized water. In fact it is this taste that makes mineral water an attractive option to drink, as distilled or other similar chemically purified waters are totally tasteless and often fail to quench thirst, because of their lack of body.
" />



        <TextView
            android:layout_width="match_parent"
            android:layout_height="wrap_content"
            android:padding="10dp"
            android:text="4.Is it safe to use mineral water for food preparation?
"
            android:textColor="@color/colorPrimary"
            android:textSize="16sp"
            android:textStyle="bold" />

        <View
            android:layout_width="match_parent"
            android:layout_height="1dp"
            android:background="@color/colorPrimaryDark" />

        <TextView
            android:textColor="@color/colorPrimary"

            android:layout_width="match_parent"
            android:layout_height="wrap_content"
            android:lineSpacingExtra="8dp"
            android:padding="15dp"
            android:text="          Mineral waters of reputed brands, which have been bottled in accordance with international regulations and packed hygienically such as JEBEL SAMHAN, AL KAUTHER, are absolutely safe to use for cooking.  As a consumer you need to satisfy yourself that the product which you are buying is indeed natural mineral water.  In some parts of the world, regulations on labeling requirements of bottled water are quite vague and many brands, which are actually processed water, try to pass themselves off as natural mineral water. The most effective way of safeguarding against being misled is to check the source of water.  For example, products which have been bottled in industrial estates or city locations are invariably processed water or bottled drinking water and not natural mineral water.
" />

        <TextView
            android:layout_width="match_parent"
            android:layout_height="wrap_content"
            android:lineSpacingExtra="8dp"
            android:padding="15dp"
            android:textColor="@color/colorPrimary"

            android:text="          Mineral water is absolutely safe for cooking, mixing of beverages and preparation of baby foods.  On boiling mineral water, it is usual for some of the minerals to be precipitated and these can often appear as white particles in the water.  Such particles should not cause any concern or worry.  The ability of water to hold minerals in suspension decreases as temperature of the water increases and so some of the minerals are precipitated when the water is heated.
" />


        <TextView
            android:layout_width="match_parent"
