            android:textColor="@color/colorPrimary"

            android:layout_width="match_parent"
            android:layout_height="wrap_content"
            android:lineSpacingExtra="8dp"
            android:padding="15dp"
            android:text="          The intake of water varies widely from person to person.  If depends on lifestyle, ambient temperature, food habits and many such variables.  Research in the US has established that at least 8 glasses (250 ml) of water is the minimum quantity that needs to be drunk daily.  You may have to adjust this quantity upwards if you do vigorous exercise, work outdoors or live in hot and dry environments and if you are pregnant or a lactating mother." />

